radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled tubular structure in the right lower quadrant in the region of the appendix with hyperenhancement of the mucosal wall measuring up to 7 mm with surrounding inflammatory changes in the fat. No evidence of distinct periappendiceal fluid collections. No free air is noted throughout the abdomen. The visualized portions of the stomach, loops of small and large bowel, spleen, bilateral adrenal glands, bilateral kidneys, liver, gallbladder, pancreas, and aorta are normal. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. Dilated appendix as described.
